(10, 14, '20095425Diagnostic-Laboratory-opt-2.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pathology department at PIC was established in December 2020 from the very first day of hospital inauguration. It was really tough as there was no preexisting laboratory and blood bank set up in the hospital. Currently the facility is organized for pathology diagnosis and delivering clinical services as well for which different sections are made and they are fully functional.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In hematology section the hematology analyzer and automated coagulation analyzer are introduced and they are running successfully now. In specialized services the Bone marrow and trephine biopsy reporting is introduced along with correction studies. Every slide of peripheral blood is considered as a patient and reviewed with expert opinion and advice whether demanded by the client or not. Uptill now we have performed 17627 tests in hematology most of which are CBC with differentials. In coagulation studies we have done 3760 tests the results of PT/APTT with INR are not challenged by any clients. Which shows lab error of less than 1%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Fully functional blood bank and transfusion services are there, started as a storage facility for RCC and FFP. Now with time platelet storage facility is also introduced. We had an MOU with the Regional Blood Centre Peshawar who is also supporting us in blood and blood components. We are now preparing our own blood components as we have purchased standard Cryofuges for the best indoor and outdoor transfusion services. The concept of rationale use of blood and blood components is applied in the PIC through hospital transfusion committee. Hem vigilance and CT ratios are monitored. For pediatric cardiology and pediatric cardiac surgery patients we have introduced cryoprecipitate a rare blood component for proper replacement of required factors in children when required. Immunohematology is performed with expert hands. Uptill now 2281 blood groups and cross matches are performed with no transfusion errors with key performance indicator maintenance, which shows very satisfactory transfusion service. Gel card for cross</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">matches are started from the very first day and we are the first public sector hospital performing cross matches on gel cards in khyberpukhtonkhwa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We have introduced hematology and anticoagulation clinic for better monitoring of warfarin in cardiac patients, national guidelines are followed in this regard, we are also focusing on the management of benign hematological disorders through this clinic. Establishment of this clinic is the first such step in any public sector hospital at KPK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Routine and special chemistry is performed on state of the art equipment like Architect from ABBOTT, all the tests are monitored through internal quality control program. The key performance indicators like critical values and turnaround time are monitored and the client is informed well in time in case of any such value. The quality of the sample tube is routinely checked and improved routinely for better results. 115890 routine chemistry tests are performed till date while 19155 special chemistry tests including immunology are performed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Microbiology section is introduced in June 2021, purchasing of incubators, safety cabinet, autoclaves were done and we are now performing wide range of cultures with further improvement in clinical pathology section, for which a semi-automated urine analyzer is also introduced with time for better reporting of urine r/e. About 1486 cultures are performed in which 159 environmental cultures are taken from OR/ICU as a part of hospital infection control programme. For COVID-19 PCR we had an MOU with Khyber medical university reference laboratory, they have allotted us with a user name and password for PIC samples, our COVID-19 counter at ER PIC is busy in sampling of all patients going for surgery or admissions, samples are registered here in PIC on KMU IPMS website and then transported to KMU lab, efforts were made for the quick results and now they are sending us the results online in next 24-36 hrs. Our staff at PIC is also availing the facility if someone is suspecting COVID-19 infection as part of infection control programme. 8753 PIC cases are reported by the reference lab till date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We have set an ideal phlebotomy services by hiring well trained staff a dedicated phlebotomy room was labelled on the ground floor near OPD for patients easy approach, we are using vacutainer and butterfly needles for our patients and we are the first in any public sector hospital at KPK for using standard needles for patient sampling. The KPIs of rejection samples and hemloysed samples are also monitored regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Now we are doing academic sessions on every Thursday and a journal club on every Tuesday. We have a very professional research environment, KMU MPHIL scholars bench training in hematology at PIC is also requested by the university, MOU is received and management is looking at its feasibility. Decision is expected in near future. In research work a pioneer paper from PIC is published by the pathology department on &ldquo;Blood Wastages&rdquo; in Indian international journal ACTA scientific, Continuous Technical Education for lab staff is routinely planned and record is kept in the lab files.</p>', '21052813Dr-Maria.jpg', 'Dr. Maria Khan', 'Assistant Professor & Acting HoD Pathology', NULL),
(11, 18, '20095445Emergency-Cadiac-Banner.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">A dedicated Cardiac specific emergency service has been established at Peshawar Institute of Cardiology, the emergency department is designated and limited&nbsp;to take care of Cardiac emergencies only with services available 24/7. The department is equiped with a dedicated,&nbsp;trained and specialized cardiac emergencies including Acute coronary syndrome (Heart Attack), Heart failure, Valvular Heart diseases, Cardiac Trauma, Post cardiac surgical patients&nbsp;and emergency congenital cardiac services.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">There has been a lot of effort put in to collaborate and establish a co-ordinated plan with the emergencies of regional and provincial hospitals along with the ambulance services for timely referal, diagnosis and treatment of cardiac patients.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">The key note for the cardiac emergency department of PIC is to establish and provide primary PCI for patients with Heart attack along with strong surgical backup for 24 hours fullfiling the most important aspect of cardiac care in the province.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Scope of Services</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Emergency services are open and available 24hours 7 days a week. The emergency is divided into 3 separate areas</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">1 Triage</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">2 Fast Track Clinic</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">3 Cardiac emergency unit and Cardiac care unit (CCU)</span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Triage</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">A designated room in emergency is available for triaging services. All patients presenting to the ER will undergo the process of Triage. Triage will be performed by a Registered Nurse. Triage involve performing rapid initial assessment of a patient.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Fast Track clinic (Filter clinic)</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">A separate room is available for non-urgent patients. Fast track&nbsp;services are designed for patients seeking care for non-acute conditions in emergency. Fast track&nbsp;clinic ensures timely patient assessment, treatment and discharge.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Cardiac emergency unit and Cardiac care unit (CCU)</span></span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Patients with cardiac emergencies are assessed, treated and disposed of in Cardiac emergency unit and Cardiac care unit. It provides evaluation and treatment to patients of various ages and varying levels of illness from minor to critical. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Both units are staffed by certified cardiologists, registered nurses and other staff. Cardiac emergency unit consist of 16 beds while Cardiac care unit (CCU) consists of 6 beds.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#555555\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Both units are well equipped with an adequate number of cardiac monitors, defibrillators, ECG Machines and ventilators.</span></span></p>', '1005242717065056Dr_abid.webp', 'Dr. Abid Ullah', 'Assistant Professor & Head of Department ( Cardiology )', NULL),
(12, 20, '20095229Nursing-Department.jpg', '<div style=\"color:#000000; font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:12pt\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">The primary goal of nurses that we must be prepared to meet diverse patient&#39;s needs, deliver exemplary safe, and quality patient care.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">We are also aware of all the difficulties and hard work required to achieve this goal, but I am very much confident that with the efforts of my very competent and enthusiastic team and with the help of Allah Almighty we can and we will achieve it easily.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">Nurses will ensure for:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">&bull; Collaboration with team to plan for patient care.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">&bull; Advocacy of health and wellbeing of patient.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">&bull; Monitoring patient health and record signs.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">&bull; Medication and treatments.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:#555555\">&bull; Patient and family&#39;s awareness about management of illnesses.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>', '29072644afsar.webp', 'Afsar Dad', 'Director Nursing', NULL),
(13, 21, '20095505pHYSIOTHERAPY-opt-2.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our comprehensive Cardiac Rehabilitation program contains specific core components. These components optimize cardiovascular risk reduction, reduce disability, encourage active and healthy lifestyle changes, and help maintain those healthy habits after rehabilitation is complete. Our Cardiac rehabilitation program is focused on:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Weight management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Blood pressure management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lipid management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Diabetes management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Tobacco cessation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Physical activity counseling</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Exercise training</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Cardiac Rehabilitation Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Cardiac rehabilitation program in the hospital is to help people who have cardiac conditions. It is designed to improve heart recovery, improve your ability to function, and prepare you for future daily activities. It is overseen by a healthcare provider. People in this program may have had a heart attack or heart surgery. Cardiac rehabilitation program in the hospital can often help you get better at your daily tasks. It may ease your symptoms and give you a sense of well-being.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Structure of CR Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Exercise program- varies from a structured, monitored program to a more independent, less monitored program</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Educational classes on lifestyle changes and disease management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Phase of Cardiac Rehabilitation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After cardiac procedures the cardiac rehab phase 1 starts and patients are treated in IPD and then follow-ups are performed in OPD of physiotherapy department. There is extensive counselling and education of patients regarding their lifestyle modification and along with counselling session there are smoking cessation sessions too. The cardiac rehab phase 2 starts immediately after hospitalization and typically comprises of 36 sessions which are telemetry monitored exercise sessions. Afterwards the cardiac rehab phase 3 starts and it contains further training sessions to prevent future heart events</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Candidates for Cardiac Rehab program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The cardiac rehab is beneficial for those who have certain heart conditions or have had certain heart procedures. It includes following. Cardiac rehabilitation at PIC typically includes a 12- week, 36-session program.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">PCI</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Angioplasty or stenting</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Post CABG</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Valve replacement surgeries</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">MI</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Pediatric surgeries &ndash; VSD/ASD Closure, TOF repair.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Advanced Rehabilitation Services</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our advanced rehabilitation services at PIC offer comprehensive and individualized rehabilitation programs for its patients. Our rehabilitation programs meet International Quality Standards such as ISO.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur rehabilitation team is highly trained and well equipped to work with sophisticated equipment. We provide an interdisciplinary team approach that includes consultations from doctors, nurses, physical therapists, and dieticians. The entire team is determined to achieve each patient&rsquo;s treatment goals. Each treatment program is designed to alleviate patients&rsquo; pain or discomfort, improve functional status and minimize the psychological effects of illnesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Facilities &amp; Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The facilities necessary to provide cardiac rehabilitation services in our department are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Dedicated staff and area for cardiac rehabilitation OPD.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">An exercise area, centrally air-conditioned, furnished with seats, LED display, state of the art equipment, patient cubicles, high-quality modalities, crash cart, and oxygen cylinder.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The highlight of our department is the installation of a Telemetry System which allows continuous monitoring of a patient&rsquo;s health condition, as well as insight into their medical history, thus improving the efficiency of physical therapy care through more effective time management. This allows a quicker response time to any risks to a patient&#39;s life or health, which improves the quality of healthcare services.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Equipment in our rehabilitation area includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bicycle ergometer</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Stationary bicycle</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Treadmill</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Elliptical</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ultrasound Machine</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Short wave diathermy</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">TENS and EMS unit</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Hydro collator and chilling unit.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Apart from Cardiac Rehabilitation our department of also offers following services and we have team of specialized physiotherapists:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Musculoskeletal rehabilitation.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Neurological rehabilitation.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Pulmonary rehabilitation.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Pediatric Rehabilitation.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sports Injury rehabilitation</li>\r\n</ul>', '25072804Dr-Waqas-Ahmed.jpg', 'Dr. Waqas Ahmed', 'Manager Physiotherapy', 'physiotherapy@pic.edu.pk'),
(14, 22, '20095523Peads-cardiology-updated.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pediatric Cardiology is the main dedicated center providing both medical and surgical facilities for entire province of KPK as well as to the patients from Afghanistan for diagnosis and treatment of both acquired and congenital heart defects in fetus, newborns, infants, children, young adults and adults with congenital heart defects (present by birth). We are the main center offering almost full range of pediatric cardiac care services in a child friendly environment with internationally established evidence based care.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This unit is fully supported by leading edge diagnostic technologies, imaging modalities like 2D, 3D, TOE and Fetal echocardiography, angiography units, operation theaters and state of the art pediatric cardiac intensive care unit. We provide 24/7 emergency services for referred patients as a single point tertiary care center along with an inpatient and outpatient facility. We provide highly individualized care for every patients as a team, to determine the best treatment options for your child, whether be it an open heart surgery or a minimal invasive procedure.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The fetal cardiac services provide services for diagnosing, counselling and management of prenatal cardiac diseases. The service has a unique role as an interface between pediatric cardiologist and obstetrician and maternal health units throughout KPK.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The purpose of catheterization laboratory is to gather evidence in the diagnosis of cardiac or pulmonary disease and to carry out interventional procedure for the non-surgical repair of congenital heart defects. Currently Procedures done in the cath lab are balloon atrial septostomy, pulmonary valvuloplasty, Aortic valvuloplasty, PDA device closure &amp; stenting, ASD &amp; VSD device closure, CoA ballooning &amp; stenting and cardiac catheterization.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pediatric heart surgeon at PIC Peshawar perform a variety of surgeries ranging from complex congenital to more common issues, all with children neurodevelopment in mind using up to date bypass techniques, thus reducing the length of stay.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our aim is to provide close collaboration between clinical services and academia. So we are the only recognized unit in KPK by the College of Physicians and Surgeons Pakistan (CPSP) for the training of fellows in Pediatric Cardiology and thus provide the services at other parts of KPK as well.</p>', '12080324DR Ijaz Hussain Associate proffessor Peds Cardiology.JPG', 'Dr. Ijaz Husain', 'Associate Professor Peads Cardiology', NULL),
(15, 23, '06105345Anesthesia-Banner.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Department of Cardiothoracic Anesthesiology is dynamic and diverse. A team of anesthesia technologists, under the guidance of the Department Head, Cardiac Anesthesiology, assists the staff anesthesiologists with a variety of clinical duties.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Departmental faculty provides care for patients undergoing a wide variety of surgical and interventional procedures which include: coronary artery bypass grafting, aortic valve repair and replacement, mitral valve repair and replacement, adult and paediatrics congenital surgery. Our faculty has a wide range of interests including perioperative medicine, critical care medicine, general anesthesiology and interventional cardiology as well as basic and clinical research.</p>', '18094345shahana.jpg', 'Dr. Shahana Raza', 'Assistant Professor & HoD Anesthesia', NULL);
INSERT INTO `management_section` (`id`, `management_id`, `header`, `description`, `hod`, `hod_name`, `hod_designation`, `hod_email`) VALUES
(16, 24, '14094633OPD Banner.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">At our Outpatient Department (OPD), we pride ourselves on delivering a wide spectrum of specialized medical services to meet the diverse healthcare needs of our patients. Our offerings include expert consultations and advanced treatments across the following specialties:</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our team of experienced and qualified doctors and healthcare professionals are committed to providing the best possible care to our patients. We understand that each patient is unique and requires individualized attention and care. We believe in a patient-centered approach and strive to provide personalized treatment plans tailored to each patient&#39;s specific needs.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our adult cardiology clinic is equipped to diagnose and treat a range of heart conditions in adults, including coronary artery disease, arrhythmias, and heart failure. We offer a range of diagnostic tests, including electrocardiograms (ECGs), echocardiograms, transoesophageal echocardiogram (TOE), exercise tolerance test (ETT), holter monitors and ambulatory blood pressure monitors to help diagnose and treat our patients&#39; heart conditions.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our adult cardiac surgery clinic offers a range of surgical procedures for the treatment of heart conditions, including coronary artery bypass grafting (CABG), valve repair or replacement surgery, and aortic aneurysm repair surgery. Our team of cardiac surgeons is highly skilled and experienced in performing these procedures using the latest techniques and technologies.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our pediatric cardiology and pediatric cardiac surgery clinics provide specialized care to children with heart conditions. We understand that children require special attention and care, and our team of pediatric cardiologists and pediatric cardiac surgeons is dedicated to providing the best possible care to our young patients.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our heart failure clinic provides comprehensive care to patients with heart failure, including diagnosis, treatment, and ongoing management. We offer a range of therapies, including medication, lifestyle modifications, and cardiac rehabilitation programs, to help our patients manage their condition and improve their quality of life.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our nephrology and pulmonology clinics offer specialized care to patients with kidney and lung conditions, respectively. Our team of nephrologists and pulmonologists is dedicated to providing the best possible care to our patients, including diagnosis, treatment, and ongoing management.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our physiotherapy clinic is equipped with state-of-the-art equipment and facilities to help patients with musculoskeletal, neurological, and other physical conditions. Our team of physiotherapists offer a range of services including cardiac rehabilitation, exercise therapy, manual therapy and electrotherapy. We work closely with each patient to develop a customized treatment plan that is tailored to their specific needs and goals.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our hematology clinic is staffed by a team of experienced hematologist who specialize in the diagnosis and treatment of blood disorders. We offer a range of services including blood tests, bone marrow aspiration and transfusions. Our team also provides counseling and support to patients and their families as they navigate the challenges of living with a blood disorder.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Our nutrition clinic offers consultations and personalized nutrition plans to help our patients improve their overall health and well-being. Our nutritionists work closely with our patients to understand their unique nutritional needs and develop personalized plans to help them achieve their health goals.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">In addition to our clinical services, our OPD also provides care to corporate panels and manages our claim section. The following corporate panels are enlisted with Peshawar Institute of Cardiology-MTI.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">State Life Insurance Corporation (Sehat Card Plus)</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Zarai Taraqiati Bank Limited (ZTBL)</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Sui Northern Gas Pipelines Limited (SNGPL)</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Jubillee Life Insurance</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Pak Qatar Takaful</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Salam Takaful</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Alfalah Insurance</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">East West Insurance</span></span></span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Askari Insurance</span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">We are committed to providing high-quality care to all our patients, and our team is always available to answer any questions or concerns you may have. Thank you for choosing Peshawar Institute of Cardiology for your healthcare needs.</span></span></span></p>', '2009182613051204Dr Ali Raza  copy.jpg', 'Dr. Ali Raza', 'Acting Incharge Outpatient & Ambulatory Services', NULL);
